<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2117" TARGET=_self>I just have to say something...</A> (Malark)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Ok first of all, ROOT works preety good at low levels....but at higher levels it does NOT...i wish all
<BR>of you would stop looking at levels 1-16 for answers because those are LOW levels. when you
<BR>acctully get to a decent level, wizards get roasted. If the 1 out of 10 chance root works then the wizard better
<BR>use ALOT of mana to kill the warrior. But if the root fails....kiss your ass goodbye wizard. The warrior
<BR>will run you down, stunning you the whole way to your death. If you are stupid enuff to stay and try and
<BR>fight him, well then youll just have a quicker death. NO WAY a wizard will get his spells across when a
<BR>warrior is chopping him up. There is just NO WAY.
<P>ok to your first post malark, you are right about the "dieing then returning with full mana". I totatly agree,
<BR>as a wizard, that we should not come back from a death with full mana. That is the only thing i am willing
<BR>to give to you Wizard Bashers. Mana should be taken away at death, OR atleast start with amount you had
<BR>when you died. The rest of the crap about ROOT, and GATE and all the other super spells we get. (YEA RIGHT)
<BR>i will not agree.
<P>Tilran -Dark Brigade-
<BR>Drow Elf Wizard
